{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"13d8a144-9fad-400f-a5a7-44aa18681420","content":"Use the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nOr filter by class name directly:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter ClassName=ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", while `=` means \"equals\". You can also combine filters, e.g. `--filter \"ClassName=ReportExporterTests&TestCategory=Unit\"`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9269b5df-407e-4101-8656-f8869a7c7895","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to run only the `ReportExporterTests` class using `dotnet test`. This is a straightforward question about dotnet CLI usage — no need to look at files.\n\nThe answer is to use the `--filter` option.","outputTokens":185,"requestId":"7035:32FCC3:80C1B:98D59:69F2AEA5"},"id":"170497e3-558d-482f-9ab3-46162426c3ee","timestamp":"2026-04-30T01:21:46.089Z","parentId":"e7e15df2-ba52-455c-b6b2-6f3291d51432"}
